    // If there are initial wins, we can improve by changing L's to W's.
    // Each L changed to W costs 1 k.
    // If an L is changed to W, it adds 1 point.
    // If this new W is adjacent to an existing W or another new W, it might convert a 1-point win to a 2-point win.
    // The most efficient way to use k changes is to fill gaps between existing W's.
    // Then, extend existing W blocks.

    std::vector<int> gap_lengths;
    int first_W = -1;
    int last_W = -1;

    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
