                                              // The first L in the gap becomes W, it gets 1 point.
                                              // The subsequent Ls in the gap become Ws, they get 2 points each.
                                              // The W after the gap was getting 1 point (if previous was L), now it gets 2 points.
                                              // So, for a gap of length `g`:
