        // If `h[h_idx]` is too far to the left of `p[p_idx]` (i.e., `h[h_idx] + T < p[p_idx]`),
        // then this head cannot cover `p[p_idx]`. We move to the next head.
        // If `h[h_idx]` is too far to the right of `p[p_idx]` (i.e., `h[h_idx] - T > p[p_idx]`),
        // then this head cannot cover `p[p_idx]`. Since `h` is sorted, no subsequent head can cover `p[p_idx]` either.
        // So, `p[p_idx]` cannot be covered. Return `false`.

        // If `h[h_idx]` can cover `p[p_idx]` (i.e., `h[h_idx] - T <= p[p_idx] <= h[h_idx] + T`):
        // This head can cover `p[p_idx]`.
        // We want to maximize the rightmost track covered by this head.
        // Let `start_pos = h[h_idx]`.
        // Let `target_pos = p[p_idx]`.
        // Time to reach `target_pos` is `abs(start_pos - target_pos)`.
        // Remaining sweep time is `T - abs(start_pos - target_pos)`.
        // The head can sweep from `target_pos` to `target_pos + remaining_sweep_time`.
        // So, the rightmost track covered by this head is `target_pos + remaining_sweep_time`.
        // We update `p_idx` to skip all tracks covered by this head.

        // Let's refine the greedy strategy for `check(T)`:
        // `p_idx = 0` (index of the first track to cover)
        // For `h_idx` from `0` to `n-1`:
        //   If `p_idx == m`, all tracks are covered, return `true`.
        //   `current_h = h[h_idx]`
        //   `first_p_to_cover = p[p_idx]`
        //
        //   // Case 1: current_h is too far to the left to cover first_p_to_cover
        //   // The head can reach up to `current_h + T`. If this is still less than `first_p_to_cover`,
        //   // then this head cannot cover `first_p_to_cover`.
        //   if (current_h + T < first_p_to_cover) {
        //       // This head cannot cover first_p_to_cover. Try next head.
        //       continue;
        //   }
        //
        //   // Case 2: current_h is too far to the right to cover first_p_to_cover
        //   // The head can reach down to `current_h - T`. If this is greater than `first_p_to_cover`,
        //   // then this head cannot cover `first_p_to_cover`.
        //   // Since `h` is sorted, all subsequent heads will be even further right.
        //   // So `first_p_to_cover` cannot be covered.
        //   if (current_h - T > first_p_to_cover) {
        //       return false;
        //   }
        //
        //   // Case 3: current_h can cover first_p_to_cover.
        //   // Calculate the rightmost point this head can cover.
        //   // The head moves to `first_p_to_cover`. Time taken: `abs(current_h - first_p_to_cover)`.
        //   // Remaining time: `T - abs(current_h - first_p_to_cover)`.
        //   // This remaining time can be used to sweep right from `first_p_to_cover`.
        //   long long rightmost_covered = first_p_to_cover + (T - std::abs(current_h - first_p_to_cover));
        //
        //   // Advance p_idx past all tracks covered by this head.
